title: Rustdoc fails to build wasm32 target documentation

labels.name: T-libs-api
labels.description: Relevant to the library API team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: A-docs
labels.description: Area: documentation for any part of the project, including the compiler, standard library, and tools

body:
When I build rust from `master` branch I catch error on documenting `std` for wasm32 target:

config.toml

```toml
optimize = true
release-debuginfo = false
assertions = false

dist-src = false
ignore-git = false
lld = false
backtrace-on-ice = true
jemalloc = false
[dist]
src-tarball = false
[target.i686-unknown-linux-gnu]
cc = "x86_64-pc-linux-gnu-gcc"
cxx = "x86_64-pc-linux-gnu-g++"
linker = "x86_64-pc-linux-gnu-gcc"
ar = "x86_64-pc-linux-gnu-ar"
llvm-config = "/usr/lib/llvm/10/bin/llvm-config"
[target.x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu]
cc = "x86_64-pc-linux-gnu-gcc"
cxx = "x86_64-pc-linux-gnu-g++"
linker = "x86_64-pc-linux-gnu-gcc"
ar = "x86_64-pc-linux-gnu-ar"
llvm-config = "/usr/lib/llvm/10/bin/llvm-config"
[target.wasm32-unknown-unknown]
linker = "lld"
```
